---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "About Hanif Carroll";
const description =
    "Learn about Hanif Carroll's path into software, the kind of products he likes to build, and the values that shape his work.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <article class="container max-w-4xl space-y-16 py-10">
        <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wide">
            <a href="/" class="transition-colors hover:text-primary">Home</a>
            <span class="text-zinc-400">/</span>
            <span class="text-primary">About</span>
        </nav>

        <header class="space-y-6">
            <span class="section-label">// About</span>
            <h1 class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl">
                Product-minded engineering, grounded in real life.
            </h1>
            <div class="tech-card p-6 md:p-8">
                <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                    I started programming in 2017 after realizing physical therapy
                    school was the wrong path for me. Since then I&rsquo;ve worked in
                    consulting, startups, and client projects, and I&rsquo;ve learned that
                    I do my best work when engineering is tied to product thinking,
                    user empathy, and clear business outcomes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </header>

        <section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="tech-card p-6 space-y-4">
                <h2 class="section-label">// Journey</h2>
                <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                    I&rsquo;ve worked at Capgemini, at LeagueApps during a strong growth
                    phase, and as a freelancer building websites and web apps. More
                    recently I&rsquo;ve built products around AI-assisted content systems,
                    community tools, and event discovery.
                </p>
                <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                    Buenos Aires has become home. Living here has shaped the way I
                    think about work, community, and the kinds of products worth
                    building.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-card p-6 space-y-4">
                <h2 class="section-label">// How I Work</h2>
                <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                    I&rsquo;m strongest in TypeScript and full-stack product work, but I
                    care as much about UX, positioning, and what users are actually
                    trying to accomplish as I do about code quality.
                </p>
                <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                    I don&rsquo;t like staying in the engineering box. I like understanding
                    the user persona, finding the main friction, and shaping the
                    product so it feels obvious to use.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="tech-card p-6 md:p-8 space-y-6">
            <h2 class="heading-display text-3xl md:text-4xl">Outside of Work</h2>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                I&rsquo;ve been lifting weights for nearly 20 years, I play ultimate
                frisbee, and I care a lot about writing, philosophy, and building
                strong in-person communities. I&rsquo;m also obsessed with how AI can help
                people perform better, not only in software engineering but in life
                more broadly.
            </p>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                If you want the current snapshot of what I&rsquo;m focused on, the
                <a href="/now/" class="underline decoration-primary underline-offset-4">now page</a>
                has the latest.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="tech-card p-6 md:p-8 space-y-4">
            <h2 class="section-label">// What I&rsquo;m Looking For</h2>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
                I like early-stage teams where I can have a real impact across
                product, engineering, and growth. The best fit is a company building
                something that genuinely helps people and has enough ambition to make
                the work matter.
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
